Package com.esri.mo2.ui.lyt Description

Contains the visual components of the layout framework application. The components include layout containers and related layout elements, such as map, legend, north arrow, scale bar, and graphics. These components are UI wrappers for their counterparts in the com.esri.mo2.map.elt package, and they are all package-private, which means that developers shouldn't worry about how these components are used. From a developer point of view, this package is being constructed around the main PageLayout class, which implements the com.esri.mo2.map.core.Layout interface, along with its supporting classes and manipulation tools. The PageLayout is a JScrollPane that contains a JLayeredPane used to manage all the element components; a set of Ruler components that manage the horizontal and vertical rulers; and a set of layout tools such as LayoutZoomIn, LayoutZoomOut, and LayoutSelect tools.

There are two types of components being used to manipulate elements: ElementPopupMenu and ElementPropertyPane. ElementPropertyPane is used to change properties associated with each individual element, while the ElementPopupMenu is used to move, group/ungroup, cut/paste, and rearrange one or more selected elements.

There is one popup menu that contains actions that apply to the PageLayout itself, and there is a LayoutActions class that defines all the actions that could be applied to the PageLayout. Developers could extract a subset of actions from it and construct a new toolbar or menu.
